#include <cstdio>
#include <cstdlib>
#include <cstring>
#include <cmath>

#include <iostream>
#include <iterator>
#include <algorithm>
#include <functional>

using namespace std;

#define C 1001

int hf[C][C] = {0};
int vf[C][C] = {0};
int sf[C][C] = {0};

int main()
{
	int m, n; scanf("%d%d\n", &m, &n);
	int sol = 0;
	for (int i = 0; i < m; i++)
	{
		char line[C];
		cin.getline(line, C, '\n');
		
		for (int j = 0; j < n; j++)
		{
			if (line[j] == '.')
			{
				hf[i][j] = (j == 0) ? 1 : hf[i][j-1]+1;
				vf[i][j] = (i == 0) ? 1 : vf[i-1][j]+1;
				
				int newc = min(hf[i][j], vf[i][j]);

				if (i == 0 || j == 0)
					sf[i][j] = 1;
				else if (newc > sf[i-1][j-1])
					sf[i][j] = sf[i-1][j-1] + 1;
				else 
					sf[i][j] = min(newc, sf[i-1][j-1]);
				
				if (sf[i][j] > sol)
					sol = sf[i][j];
			}
			else
				hf[i][j] = vf[i][j] = sf[i][j] = 0;
		}
	}
	if (sol == 0)
		cout << -1 << endl;
	else
		cout << sol * sol << endl;
	
	return 0;
}
